SIMPLE: brazen
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Brazen
<hw>Bra"zen</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos><ety>[OE.
<ets>brasen</ets>, AS. <ets>br⟦ae⟧sen</ets>. See <er>Brass</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Pertaining to, made of, or resembling, brass.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Sounding harsh and loud, like resounding
brass.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Impudent; immodest; shameless; having a front like
brass; <as>as, a <ex>brazen</ex> countenance</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Brazen age</b></col>. <sd>(a)</sd> <fld>(Myth.)</fld>
<cd>The age of war and lawlessness which succeeded the silver age.</cd>
<sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Arch⟦ae⟧ol.)</fld> <cd>See under
<er>Bronze</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Brazen sea</b></col> <fld>(Jewish
Antiq.)</fld>, <cd>a large laver of brass, placed in Solomon's temple
for the use of the priests.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brazen</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Brazen
<hw>Bra"zen</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Brazened</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Brazening</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To carry through impudently or
shamelessly; <as>as, to <ex>brazen</ex> the matter through</as>.</def>
<-- = brass it out -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sabina <qex>brazened</qex> it out before Mrs. Wygram, but inwardly
she was resolved to be a good deal more circumspect.</q> <rj><qau>W.
Black.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brazen-browed</ent>⟦br⟧
